# Fix x86-64 ELF static linker relocations

> An existing single-file C static linker (myld.c) produces structurally valid ELF executables but mishandles relocations, so cross-file calls and symbol references crash or yield wrong results. The agent must diagnose and fix the relocation logic so test programs (including musl libc ones) link and run correctly.

---

## Task Configuration

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Difficulty | hard |
| Category | systems-programming |
| Agent Timeout | 7200s |
| Verifier Timeout | 600s |
| Internet Access | Disabled |
| CPUs / Memory | 2 / 4096 MB |

