### Reward Hacking

| Check | Status | Detail |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Noop Baseline | PASS | Baseline myld has buggy relocations so all tier tests fail; reward sums to 0.0. |
| Adversarial Audit | WARN | Anti-gaming source-text gate is trivially bypassable; agent can shell out to ld/gcc via execve or indirected execvp without matching any banned literal. |
| Agent Code As User | PASS | All make/link/run steps run via 'su agent -s /bin/bash -c env -i …' inside strace. |
| Strace Tracing | PASS | strace -f wraps build and every link/run job; log is grepped for openat write/create on reward.{txt,json} before scoring and triggers fail_with. |
| Verifier Protected | PASS | compute_reward.py runs outside strace as root, only reads /logs/verifier/test_results.json and /app/myld.c as text — never imports from /app. |
| Fault Tolerance | PASS | EXIT trap guarantees reward.txt exists, fail_with always exits 0, strace and per-link runs use timeout wrappers, atomic reward write via os.replace. |

**Undefended Attack Vectors**
- **HIGH**: Bypass the 'no shelling out to ld/gcc' anti-gaming gate by using execve(), posix_spawn(), or execvp with a variable-typed program-name argument — none match the literal BANNED_PATTERNS substrings — to wrap the real system linker and pass every tier. — *Fix: Replace text-pattern scanning with an actual behavioral check (e.g., run myld under strace and fail if it execve()s anything other than itself), or at minimum extend BANNED_PATTERNS to cover execve, posix_spawn, fexecve, and ban any reference to /usr/bin/ld, /usr/bin/gcc, musl-gcc as string literals.*
**Acknowledged / Acceptable Gaps**
- Agent can modify its own strace/agent logs in /logs/agent before verification. — Documented Harbor limitation — agent trace tampering is not preventable in the single-container model and is irrelevant to scoring, which uses /logs/verifier only.
- Test source .c/.S files remain readable in /app/tests so the agent can in principle precompute expected outputs. — The .ref binaries are removed from /app and live root-only in /tests/refdata; even with predicted outputs, the agent must still produce a working ELF and avoid the shell-out gate, so this alone does not inflate score.

**Existing Defenses**
- **Filesystem lockdown**: /tests chmod 700 root-only; /tests/refdata chmod go-rwx so .o/.a/.ref are unreadable to agent; /logs/verifier chmod 700 + rm -rf as first step of test.sh
- **Privilege separation**: agent user owns only /app and OUTDIR; build + link + run all dropped to agent via su -s /bin/bash -c env -i; verifier and scoring run as root outside agent reach
- **Runtime auditing**: strace -f traces clone/fork/execve/openat for every agent invocation; openat() with O_WRONLY|O_RDWR|O_CREAT on reward.{txt,json} flips REWARD_TAMPER and forces fail_with
- **Input integrity**: Pristine .o/.a staged from root-only /tests/refdata into a fresh mktemp dir per run; STAGE chowned root:root 755 + files 644 so agent can read but not swap inputs; OUTDIR is the only agent-writable surface during the agent phase
- **Process isolation**: pkill -9 -u agent before agent phase, between phases, and before grading; strace -f blocks until all descendants exit so no daemon survives into root grading

### Reward Design

| Check | Status | Detail |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Correctness Gating | WARN | Baseline myld.c is described as already linking the simplest cases, so T1 likely scores 0.08 unmodified, above the <0.01 ideal. |
| Implementation Agnostic | PASS | Scoring is purely behavioural: link with the agent's myld, run the ELF, diff stdout/exit against a root-owned reference binary — any working linker passes. |
| Dimension Balance | PASS | Tiers are weighted by difficulty (T1 0.08 → T5 0.40) and gated by behavioural correctness, so the agent cannot game easy tiers to dominate — T5 alone is 40% and requires real relocation correctness. |
| Shortcut Resistant | PASS | Trivial myld (empty ELF, copy input, constant output) fails the diff against per-test reference outputs and the readelf structural gates, scoring near 0; a MIN_CODE_LINES=150 and banned-pattern gate also blocks shelling out to ld/gcc. |
| Modular Scoring | PASS | compute_reward.py reads only /logs/verifier/test_results.json and /app/myld.c as text and can be re-run independently of agent execution. |
| Reward Json Schema | PASS | Both the success path and --fail path write reward.json with score (float), subscores (list, populated on failure with zeros), and additional_data, plus reward.txt. |

**Reward Formula**: `score = 0 if anti_gaming_fail else sum(weight_t * pass_fraction_t for t in [T1=0.08, T2=0.12, T3=0.16, T4=0.24, T5=0.40])`
Tiered weighted sum over 5 difficulty tiers of relocation/linker correctness, zeroed by an anti-gaming source gate.

| Component | Metric | Gate / Weight |
|-----------|--------|---------------|
| T1 basic ELF | pass fraction over [t1_t1_exit run diff, t1_t1_exit_elf readelf gate] | diff vs ref + structural readelf / 0.08 |
| T2 cross-file linking | pass fraction over [t2_t2_hello, t2_t2_data, t2_t2_hello_elf] | diff vs ref + structural readelf / 0.12 |
| T3 bss + archive | pass fraction over [t3_t3_bss, t3_t3_archive] | diff vs ref / 0.16 |
| T4 structural + musl hello | pass fraction over [t4_entry, t4_sections, t4_nostdlib, t4_hello_libc] | readelf structural + diff vs ref / 0.24 |
| T5 complex musl | pass fraction over [t5_printf, t5_multi, t5_common] | diff vs ref / 0.40 |
| anti-gaming gate | no banned exec patterns + min 150 non-blank lines in myld.c (oracle-bypassed via secret marker) | multiplicative — zeroes total on violation / gate (×0 on fail) |

### Fairness

| Check | Status | Detail |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Instruction Verifier Sync | PASS | Verifier tiers T1-T5 (single .o, cross-file calls, .bss/archives, musl libc) match the tier progression and tasks explicitly described in instruction.md. |
| Definitions Documented | PASS | All terms (ELF relocations, .o/.a, PC-relative vs absolute, musl CRT order) are either documented in instruction.md or standard x86-64/ELF domain knowledge. |
| Tools Accessible | PASS | Dockerfile installs gcc, musl-tools, build-essential, strace, readelf/objdump (binutils); Makefile and myld.c scaffold are present in /app workspace. |
| Oracle Exists | PASS | solution/solve.sh exists (152 lines) and uses the HARBOR_ORACLE_FLAG marker to bypass the anti-gaming source gate. |
| Hidden Test Fairness | PASS | Hidden structural checks (entry nonzero, .text present, no .dynsym/.dynstr) are standard correctness properties of a static ELF executable, not new requirements. |

